  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nPoW verification is computationally expensive (even for high-performant languages like Go)\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\ninstead of verifying the PoW on every header, geth does so on a randomly chosen subset of them, in a way that the\r\nprobability of a forgery is smaller than the probability of an attacker producing a SHA3 collision.",
